      "writtenOn": "2017-12-21T20:25:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "static\n\n(unfortunately, C++ requires a local copy to be made otherwise, because its address is taken on the next line, and without static, each activation of a function needs unique addresses. clang doesn’t implement this properly, but it may be fixed in the future. GCC does implement this properly. “static” allows compiler to just use the address of the real const data, without any copies.)",
